AI:
==
Any method that tries to replicate the results of some aspect of human cognition.

ML:
====
Programs that performs better with experience.
It is explicitly not rule-based.
Simple definition - Using data to answer questions.
Study of computer algorithms that improve automatially through experience.(means data)
It figures out the rules for itself.

ANN:(Artifical Neural Networks)
===============================
A Machine learning algorithm

Deep Learning:
=============
A type of ANN
It's a particular subset of machine learning itself.

Big Data
========
Using data to find unobvious patterns

