When is machine learning useful?
================================
When experts are unable to explain their expertise
 - Image recognition
 - Speech recognition
 - Driving a car
 
 Rule of thumb
 =============
 Don't use if rules are concise and clear
 
 
 A Fundamental "trick" in most of ML
 ====================================
 All problems are data, all solutions are functions/maps
 
 For example, whether it is a face recognition problem, spam recognition problem,fluid mechanics problem, whatever it's, every problem can be posted can be posed as a data problem.
 
